President Obama has nominated Judge Marco Hernandez, Beryl A. Howell, Judge Steve C. Jones, Judge Diana Saldaña, and Michael H. Simon to seats on the United States District Court. Judge Hernandez is currently a Circuit Court judge in Oregon with 15 years of experience. Beryl A. Howell serves as a Member of the U.S. Sentencing Commission and has a background in law and litigation consulting. Judge Steve C. Jones is a Judge of the Tenth Superior Court District in Georgia and has been in this position since 1995. Judge Diana Saldaña is a United States Magistrate Judge in Texas and has held this position since 2006. Michael H. Simon is a partner in a law firm in Oregon and specializes in business litigation.